concepts exploring the /proc directory for process information

1) accessing the process infrmation
/proc/<pid> -> you will get the directory or file

2) comman proc commads directory
/proc/<pid>/status -> youwill get the full information about that process
cat /proc/<pid>/status -> same as above command

3) current working directory (cwd)
readlink  /proc/<pid>/cwd

4) to get load average information
cat /proc/loadavg

5) to get cpu information
cat /proc/cpuinfo

6) to get memory information
cat /proc/meminfo
 
7) to check the commend line argument is there are not

cat /proc/<pid>/cmdline


